The paper discusses the impact of output activation functions on learning and performance in classification tasks, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The experiments are conducted on image classification (cs.CV) and semantic segmentation (cs.CL) tasks, which further support these categories. The paper also discusses the role of exponentiation in boosting gradients, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
